instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands generated by the Digital Twin (e.g., HVAC setpoints, lighting levels, actuator activations) are emitted as JSON payloads via Ditto’s command interface. These messages are routed through Eclipse Hono to the device gateways, which translate them into the device‑specific protocol used by the Building Control System (e.g., BACnet, Modbus, or OPC UA). Command messages are validated against a schema, authenticated through Ditto’s security module (using OAuth 2.0 or JWT tokens signed by the tenant’s authority), and authorised according to the user role (Facility Manager or DT Engineer). Feedback is collected by the physical devices and sent back through the same channel as telemetry updates, which overwrite the twin’s “status” or “execution_state” properties to confirm command execution or report failures. In cases of conflicting commands, a central conflict‑resolution service applies predefined priority rules (e.g., manual override has precedence) and logs the resolution. Execution confirmations are explicitly acknowledged by the gateway sending an ACK message that updates the twin’s state."
]

